
Principle:

    S - Single-responsiblity Principle -> a class should have only one job.
    O - Open-closed Principle -> open for extension, closed for modification.
    L - Liskov Substitution Principle ->  every subclass or derived class should be substitutable for their base or parent class.
    I - Interface Segregation Principle
    D - Dependency Inversion Principle -> This principle allows for decoupling.

References:
1.
https://www.digitalocean.com/community/conceptual_articles/s-o-l-i-d-the-first-five-principles-of-object-oriented-design#toc-single-responsibility-principle